<br>
2.) Absolutely, positively, don't tell me if you want your cappucino decaf. Make sure you stand there and watch me make it, taking me a full minute or so to steam the milk and brew the espresso, and an additional few seconds to make the foam cap. You've given me a full two minutes to make the drink, so make sure you wait until I HAND it to you before you say, &quot;You made this decaf, right?&quot; Forget about asking me to make it decaf BEFORE I made it, or hell, even DURING making it. I'd much rather you sit there and watch me do it wrong for a full two minutes. <br>
<br>
3.) I love it when you ask me to put the cream cheese on your bagel for you. Even though they are in little to-go containers with plastic knives for you to do it yourself, I like to be your personal slave and open up the container and spread it on for you so you don't have to do it. Would you like me to put the sugar in your coffee for you as well, m'am?<br>
<br>
4.) Under ALL circumstances, NEVER call in a huge order ahead of time. Especially when we have a line of 15 people out the door of the building. The procedure we prefer is for you to come up and ask for two dozen bagles, all sliced, while there are 15 other people in line after you simply wanting a cup of coffee or a pastry. It's also best to NOT know what kind of bagels you want in the boxes, and just tell us to pick for you, since we employees of Panera also excel as mind readers.<br>
<br>
5.) When you are waiting in line, please, under NO circumstances be deciding what it is you would like from the bakery. Sure, you can see everything from where you stand in line, but we like it when you wait until you get up to the counter and stand there with your nose pressed against the glass and take 5 minutes to decide.<br>
<br>
6.) Always, ALWAYS, when you ask for a drink made with skim milk, get the whipped cream added. That makes a lot of sense.<br>
<br>
